<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State (
                        Stettinius
                    ) to the President</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Malta</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d149</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">149</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1944-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1944-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.01/11–2644</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SERJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-28">November 28,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the President</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Resignation of <persName corresp="#p_MS1">Mikolajczyk</persName>
                </p>
                <p>I think you will be interested in looking at the two enclosed telegrams in regard
                    to the Polish situation, the first reporting a conversation between <persName corresp="#p_MS1">Mikolajczyk</persName> and Schoenfeld in which the former
                    explained in some detail his reasons for resigning<note n="1" xml:id="d149fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_210">pp. 210</ref>–<ref target="#pg_212">212</ref>.</note> and the latter quoting extensively
                    from British press discussion of the subject.<note n="2" xml:id="d149fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> You will notice that a number of British papers erroneously
                    attribute <persName corresp="#p_MS1">Mikolajczyk</persName>’s resignation to our
                    refusal to guarantee Polish frontiers.</p>
                <p>In order to counteract the London news stories regarding the frontier guarantee,
                    the Department on November 25 released the following statement:</p>
                <p>The specific question of the guarantee of the Polish frontier by this Government
                    was not and could not have been an issue since this Government’s traditional
                    policy of not guaranteeing specific frontiers in Europe is well known.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward</hi> R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius,
                                Jr</hi>.</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
